# ── Credential safety: never commit secrets, vaults, keyfiles, or backups ──
# Belt-and-suspenders — the vault normally lives in ~/.paladin (outside the
# repo), but this guarantees that even a vault/keyfile/backup created INSIDE the
# checkout can never be staged. Enforced by tests/test_no_credentials_tracked.py.
*.paladin
*.warden
vault.paladin
vault.warden
.paladin/
.warden/
paladin-backup-*.zip
*-backup-*.zip
*.pre-restore
# env files (allow committed *.example / *.template / *.sample only)
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
!*.env.example
!*.env.template
!*.env.sample
secrets/
!secrets/README.md
!secrets/.gitkeep
# private keys / keyfiles
*.pem
*.key
id_rsa
id_ed25519
*.keyfile
# runtime state that can hold amounts / ids
skills/**/state/
custodian/bundled_skills/**/state/

